ef=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/5-ways-to-transform-banking-into-a-service\/#4-allow-your-baas-clients-to-self-serve\" title=\"4. Allow Your Baas Clients to Self Serve\">4. Allow Your Baas Clients to Self Serve<\/a><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-3'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-5\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/5-ways-to-transform-banking-into-a-service\/#5-use-closed-loop-functionality-to-track-and-address-customer-feedback\" title=\"5. Use Closed-Loop Functionality to Track and Address Customer Feedback\">5. Use Closed-Loop Functionality to Track and Address Customer Feedback<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/li><li class='ez-toc-page-1 ez-toc-heading-level-2'><a class=\"ez-toc-link ez-toc-heading-6\" href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/5-ways-to-transform-banking-into-a-service\/#loyalty-trust-it-all-comes-down-to-the-experiences-of-your-internet-banking-clients\" title=\"Loyalty &amp; Trust \u2013 It All Comes Down to the Experiences of Your Internet Banking Clients\">Loyalty &amp; Trust \u2013 It All Comes Down to the Experiences of Your Internet Banking Clients<\/a><\/li><\/ul><\/nav><\/div>\n<h2 id=\"1-collect-client-experience-data-in-realtime-across-all-digital-payments-channels\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"1-collect-client-experience-data-in-realtime-across-all-digital-payments-channels\"><\/span>1. Collect Client Experience Data in Realtime Across All Digital Payments Channels<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The first step banks need to take to transform banking, and the <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-multiple-payment-gateways-help-merchants-sell\/#:~:text=Anyone%20looking%20to%20expand%20their%20business%20to%20a%20global%20scale%20should%20consider%20whether%20their%20current%20payment%20provider%20can%20handle%20such%20a%20shift\">digital payments<\/a> sector is to understand their customers&#8217; thinking.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s a move that requires them to deploy surveys that can help them gather feedback across all their online banking channels.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Examples of how to do this include:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Relationship feedback: A relationship survey allows a <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/baas-explained-comparison-of-baas-service-providers\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"474\">Baas <\/a>company to understand their clients&#8217; thoughts about their services. The input will shed light on whether client needs are being met.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Mobile &amp; website feedback: Most customers interact with internet banking companies via a computer or mobile app. Ensuring they have a user-friendly system will ensure that they keep coming back.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Customer support feedback: Missing a mortgage payment, filing a claim, or losing a <strong>credit\/debit card <\/strong>are emotional experiences. You need to ensure that the company reps can take care of the company&#8217;s needs.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"2-identify-the-most-common-baas-requests\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"2-identify-the-most-common-baas-requests\"><\/span>2. Identify the Most Common Baas Requests<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Identifying the common service requests will require determining which areas you can use to create a caring and <a href=\"https:\/\/www.forbes.com\/sites\/forbesbusinesscouncil\/2021\/11\/12\/adding-soul-for-a-great-customer-experience-in-banking\/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">connected banking experience<\/a>.<br>Focus on common service requests such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Ordering checks<br>\u2022 Reporting a lost credit card<br>\u2022 Frequent technical issues, e.g.,<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>o How to reset a digital payments systems password<br>o How to unlock an account<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>For example, your customers may be calling the bank because you don&#8217;t have other support alternatives, such as an online chatbot.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Such routine inquiries and processes are a great starting point, especially when introducing automation. They will help in transforming your banking services.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"3-make-your-online-banking-systems-speak-one-language\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"3-make-your-online-banking-systems-speak-one-language\"><\/span>3. Make Your Online Banking Systems Speak One Language<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p><br>For most Baas clients, online self-service bots and contact centres are the only way to interact with a bank.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Therefore, it&#8217;s necessary to ensure there&#8217;s a connection between the contact centre and the other teams, data sources, and departments.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Contact centre operations typically thrive from the context derived from answering questions such as:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 What is the name of this client?<br>\u2022 Has the system properly authenticated the client?<br>\u2022 For how many years have they banked with the company?<br>\u2022 What products and digital payments services do they usually use?<br>\u2022 How can the contact centre solve their issue?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The data to answer these questions will come from the connections made through core system integration, authentication, and CRM segmentation.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>To ensure the digital payments systems are speaking in one language, contact centre leaders will need to shift their focus to:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 Providing one platform where the teams can perform all tasks in a single environment<br>\u2022 Improved customer engagement through social media and mobile apps<br>\u2022 Try to boost productivity by encouraging automation<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"4-allow-your-baas-clients-to-self-serv\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"4-allow-your-baas-clients-to-self-serve\"><\/span>4. Allow Your Baas Clients to Self Serve<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Today&#8217;s customers have become increasingly self-reliant. The digital payments services have conditioned them to find what they want when they want.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>As a result, they have learned to yearn for such experiences. Some even expect to encounter them when using internet banking solutions.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Whether searching for a product or changing the account settings, customers find that having the ability to do so is convenient and efficient.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>It&#8217;s particularly true when you look at the impact that the COVID-19 pandemic has had on the consumer banking industry.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The pandemic has limited in-branch and in-person service, forcing clients to adopt mobile and digital banking.<br>Allowing self-service is a great way to transform banking into service, as most credit unions and banks currently don&#8217;t support this option.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from easy access to product information, clients also want easy access to answers to frequent questions like:<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>\u2022 What is the bank&#8217;s routing number?<br>\u2022 What process should one follow when <a href=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/how-to-transfer-money-internationally\/\" data-type=\"post\" data-id=\"478\">transferring money<\/a>?<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" loading=\"lazy\" width=\"800\" height=\"400\" src=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/payment_trend1.jpg\" alt=\"Digital Banking\" class=\"wp-image-603\" srcset=\"http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/payment_trend1.jpg 800w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/payment_trend1-300x150.jpg 300w, http:\/\/localhost:8080\/wp-content\/uploads\/2022\/01\/payment_trend1-768x384.jpg 768w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 800px) 100vw, 800px\" \/><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 id=\"5-use-closed-loop-functionality-to-track-and-address-customer-feedback\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"5-use-closed-loop-functionality-to-track-and-address-customer-feedback\"><\/span>5. Use Closed-Loop Functionality to Track and Address Customer Feedback<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Poor phone call support, social media complaints, and low NPS scores can alert banking facilities to negative customer experiences.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Online banking facilities can now receive automated mobile or web notifications suggesting poor experiences. They can use these notifications to close the loop or take the desired action.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Additionally, they can use the experience management system to track and manage all customer engagements. It makes it easier to ensure all complaints get resolved.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Apart from resolving and addressing complaints, the banks can use these systems to train their employees on how to react in future instances.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the end, the degree to which a customer experience program is successful is determined by its ability to improve customer experiences. Ensuring your employees have real-time metrics on their hands will make this a possibility.<br>It can also assist in improving the client&#8217;s and banks&#8217; financial outcomes.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 id=\"loyalty-trust-it-all-comes-down-to-the-experiences-of-your-internet-banking-clients\"><span class=\"ez-toc-section\" id=\"loyalty-trust-it-all-comes-down-to-the-experiences-of-your-internet-banking-clients\"><\/span>Loyalty &amp; Trust \u2013 It All Comes Down to the Experiences of Your Internet Banking Clients<span class=\"ez-toc-section-end\"><\/span><\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>A customer experience study conducted by Forbes shows that clients want to feel valued and appreciated.<br>Baas clients who feel valued by a brand will advocate for it among their peers. When clients have a good experience, the brand builds a long-term relationship with them.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In the future, these clients will freely recommend the digital payments products and services your company offers. This will create more value for your business.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The five tips above can help <strong>transform banking into service<\/strong>, 